## Branches — `<%= @project.full_path %>`

Manage branches for this project repository. All requests require a personal access token passed in the `PRIVATE-TOKEN` header.

**Base URL:** <%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>

**Authentication:**

```bash
curl "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/repository/branches" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

---

### List Branches

```bash
curl "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/repository/branches" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

**Query parameters:**

- `search` (optional) — Filter branches by name substring
- `regex` (optional) — Filter branches by RE2 regular expression matched against branch name
- `sort` (optional) — Sort order (e.g. `name_asc`, `name_desc`, `updated_asc`, `updated_desc`)
- `page` (optional) — Page number (default: `1`)
- `per_page` (optional) — Items per page, max `100` (default: `20`)

**Response fields per branch:**

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `name` | Branch name |
| `default` | Whether this is the default branch |
| `protected` | Whether this branch is protected |
| `merged` | Whether the branch tip is an ancestor of the default branch |
| `state` | Branch state |
| `last_commit` | Last commit object (`id`, `short_id`, `title`, `author_name`, `authored_date`) |

**Pagination headers returned:**

| Header | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `X-Total` | Total number of branches |
| `X-Total-Pages` | Total number of pages |
| `X-Page` | Current page |
| `X-Per-Page` | Items per page |
| `X-Next-Page` | Next page number (empty if on last page) |
| `X-Prev-Page` | Previous page number (empty if on first page) |

---

### Check if a Branch Exists

```bash
curl -I "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/repository/branches/:name" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

- `:name` — Branch name
- Returns `204 No Content` if the branch exists
- Returns `404 Not Found` if the branch does not exist

---

### Get a Single Branch

```bash
curl "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/repository/branches/:name" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

- `:name` — Branch name (URL-encoded if it contains slashes, e.g. `feature%2Fmy-branch`)
- Returns `404 Not Found` if the branch does not exist

---

### Create a Branch

```bash
curl -X POST "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/repository/branches" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"branch": "feature-new", "ref": "main"}'
```

**Fields:**

- `branch` (required) — Name of the new branch
- `ref` (required) — Branch name, tag, or commit SHA to create the branch from

Returns `201 Created` with the branch object on success.
Returns `400 Bad Request` if `branch` or `ref` is missing or the ref does not exist.

---

### Delete a Branch

```bash
curl -X DELETE "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/repository/branches/:name" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

- `:name` — Branch name (URL-encoded if it contains slashes)

Returns `204 No Content` on success.
Returns `403 Forbidden` if the branch is protected or is the default branch.
Returns `404 Not Found` if the branch does not exist.
